# Styling (Uniwind)

Neuland Next uses **Uniwind** (Tailwind CSS v4 for React Native). Use `className` on React Native primitives.

## Essentials

- **Entry**: `src/global.css` imported in `src/app/_layout.tsx` (never in Expo `index`)
- **Metro**: `metro.config.js` — `withUniwindConfig` must be the outermost wrapper
- **Tokens**: `@theme` + `@layer theme` / `@variant light|dark` in `global.css`; mirror `src/styles/themes.ts`
- **Theme sync**: `useUniwindThemeSync` in `provider.tsx` — do not duplicate preference logic
- **Helpers**: `@/utils/uniwind-utils` (`hairlineBorder`, `toColor`)
- **Styled wrappers**: `@/components/Universal/styled` for FlashList, BottomSheet, expo-image
- **Types**: run `bun uniwind:types` after changing `global.css`

```tsx
// Typical pattern
<View className="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-page">
  <Text className="text-text text-base">…</Text>
</View>
```

- Platform variants: `ios:`, `android:`, `web:`
- Runtime colors: `useCSSVariable('--color-primary')` from `uniwind`
- Dark mode check: `useUniwind()` → `theme === 'dark'`

## When `className` is not enough — use `StyleSheet` / inline `style`

Prefer `className` on React Native primitives (`View`, `Text`, `Pressable`, …). When Uniwind
cannot target a component, fall back to React Native `StyleSheet.create` or inline `style`.

**Use the fallback for:**

- Third-party components that don't accept `className` (e.g. `LinearGradient`, Reanimated views)
- Wrapped third-party components — add to `@/components/Universal/styled` via `withUniwind`, or use `style`
- Passing resolved classes to children that only accept `style`: `useResolveClassNames('text-text text-base')`
- Reanimated animations, dynamic dimensions, hairline borders (`hairlineBorder`), per-item dynamic colors

```tsx
import { StyleSheet } from 'react-native'
import { LinearGradient } from 'expo-linear-gradient'

// Third-party: className is ignored — use StyleSheet
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
	eventLine: {
		borderBottomStartRadius: 5,
		borderTopStartRadius: 5,
		width: 4
	}
})

<LinearGradient colors={[a, b]} style={styles.eventLine} />

// RN primitive: className + dynamic color in style
<View className="flex-1 flex-row" style={{ backgroundColor: primaryColor }}>
```

Do not put `className` on a third-party component and assume it works — verify or use `style`.

## Avoid

- NativeWind, styled-components, or raw Tailwind config files outside `global.css`
- Hard-coded colors/sizes — use theme tokens
- Editing `src/uniwind-types.d.ts` by hand
- Importing `global.css` in the Expo entry file (breaks HMR)

